<h2>Strategies</h2>

<p>If you are a first time user, we strongly urge you to read the financial planning and asset allocation sections. These are the most important foundation for your success in financial investment.</p>

<p>Once you identify your overall strategies, you now could proceed to individual asset class investment strategies.</p>

<p>In ValidFi, a strategy is constructed using a time based programming language with Java syntax.  A strategy could be associated with several model portfolios. It could be also used for other portfolios. ValidFi provides rich APIs for manipulating the underlying portfolio and initiate buy/sell trading methods. It provides many technical indicators. Furthermore, linking to third party libraries such as the open source R is provided to access to powerful time series and statistical functions. The classes of ValidFi's strategies are shown in Figure 2. </p>

<p>The following are the classes of strategies. Click on the links to get more information for each class. </p>
