<p>Financial planning has two major components: cash flow strategies and estate planning. Cash flow strategies are for your long term cash flow needs while estate planning is for your long lasting wealth. The outcome of the planning is a workable plan for investment portfolios with clear return and risk factors identified.</p>

<p>ValidFi offers a collection of cash flow investment strategies. The typical examples are the retirement withdrawal rate strategies in good time and bad time. Value averaging and dollar cost average are strategies on how to invest in the risky asset classes such as stock markets with a (planned) stream of cash income.</p>

