<h2>Portfolio Center</h2>

<p>There are two types of portfolios in ValidFi. Strategies could have one or many so called 'model portfolios'. These model portfolios are created to monitor their strategies. Since a strategy could have parameters and various time period, multiple model portfolios could be created for each combination.</p>
<p>The second type of portfolios are for general purpose. Users create these portfolios with multiple strategies or even multiple portfolios. Unlike other stock/commodity trading systems, ValidFi treats portfolio level asset allocation, rebalancing and asset classes (which are commonly used in today's institutional investment practice) as first class citizens. It provides place holders for specifying portfolio level strategies, asset classfications and individual asset class strategies. </p>

<p>As a service to our members, ValidFi also follows a list of <a target="_blank" href="../ajax/${HomeURL}ModelPortfolios&&includeHeader=true">model portfolios.</a></p>

<p>ValidFi also provides <a href="../portfolio/Main.action">a table of all private and public portfolios with search capability.</a> The private portfolios are those created by users and they are for private use. The public portfolios include users created public portfolios and those provided by ValidFi. </p>

